Maintainer: Debangan Dey <ddey1@alumni.jh.edu>
Description: Joint covariance estimation and multivariate functional principal
    component analysis (M2FPCA) for multivariate mixed-type functional data
    (continuous, truncated, ordinal, and binary) measured on a common grid,
    based on the latent Semiparametric Gaussian Copula process. Estimates
    marginal and cross-covariance surfaces between functional variables of
    possibly different types, a partially separable multivariate
    Karhunen-Loeve representation, and multivariate principal-component scores.
    Builds on the single-variable estimator in the 'SGCTools' package and
    handles regular and irregular (sparse / asynchronous) sampling. Methods
    described in Dey, Ghosal, Merikangas and Zipunnikov (2026)
    <arXiv:2603.11385>.
